| **Secrets stored in plaintext repository path (`secrets/api-keys/github.txt`)** | 🔴 CRITICAL | Audit full Git history for secrets exposure; mandate migration to dedicated secrets management platform (Vault/AWS Secrets Manager) as pre-close condition |
| **Reviewed codebase is prototype-grade with no production-ready components** | 🔴 CRITICAL | Immediately expand diligence scope to cover full production codebase; confirm reviewed code is non-production component; do not allow this finding to stand unresolved at deal close |
| **No authentication or authorization on any API endpoint** | 🔴 HIGH | Require roadmap and timeline for auth implementation; verify production systems have authentication; treat as pre-close blocker for any customer-facing integration |
| **No test coverage in reviewed codebase** | 🔴 HIGH | Require full test coverage report for production systems; cross-reference with SOC 2 SDLC control evidence; set minimum coverage threshold as integration milestone |
| **Java core engine legacy debt with Rust rewrite at 60% completion** | 🟠 HIGH | Commission independent technical assessment of Rust rewrite scope and timeline; negotiate milestone-based earnout tied to Rust engine delivery |
| **CTO L. Zhang key-person dependency (3/14 patents, rewrite leadership)** | 🟠 HIGH | Negotiate individual retention agreement with milestone vesting; conduct IP assignment verification for all 14 patents; assess patent defensibility without Zhang |
| **No input validation; manual JSON via string interpolation** | 🟠 HIGH | Mandate security-focused code review of all production APIs; require remediation plan before customer data integration begins |
| **Customer concentration: top 5 customers = 38% ARR** | 🟠 HIGH | Review all customer contracts for change-of-control provisions; develop customer retention playbook for top 5 accounts; consider earn-out structure tied to customer retention |
| **SOC 2 Type II certification integrity post-repository compromise** | 🟠 HIGH | Obtain full SOC 2 audit report; assess whether compromise is a reportable incident; engage certification auditor to confirm scope and status |
| **No observability, logging, or metrics infrastructure visible** | 🟠 MEDIUM | Require production observability architecture documentation; verify monitoring platform integration for all customer-facing services |
| **In-memory data storage with no persistence or thread safety** | 🟠 MEDIUM | Confirm this component is non-production; verify production persistence architecture independently |
| **FTC second request risk at ~22% combined market share** | 🟠 MEDIUM | Engage regulatory counsel immediately; prepare HSR filing strategy; model 6–12 month deal timeline extension in retention and integration planning |
| **No pagination on list endpoints** | 🟡 LOW | Standard remediation; low risk if production systems handle pagination appropriately |
